## Quick Reference

| Trigger | Required Action |
|---------|-----------------|
| "implement X" | **MCP first**, then full checklist |
| "create X" | **MCP first**, then full checklist |
| "modify X" | **MCP first**, then full checklist |
| "fix bug" | **MCP first** (Context7 + Sequential Thinking), then systematic debugging |
| "add feature" | **MCP first**, then brainstorm + plan |
| "continue" | **MCP first** (query relevant MCPs), show summary, proceed |
| "/continue" | Same as "continue" - MCP consultation is mandatory |

## Exceptions

Skip MCP + checklist ONLY for:
- Trivial edits (typos, comments, formatting)
- Reading/exploring code (no changes)
- Answering questions (no implementation)
- User explicitly says "skip MCP"

**Default: ALWAYS query MCPs first. Show what you learned. Then implement.**
